WorkItem.Description:
If a cell contains rich text (e.g. superscript), Cell::getFormattedValue returns a RichText object instead of a string (as it should be the case according to its PHPDoc method signature). To fix this bug, just cast the result to a string:
Â 
	/**
	 * Get cell value with formatting
	 *
	 * @return string
	 */
	public function getFormattedValue()
	{
		return (string) PHPExcel_Style_NumberFormat::toFormattedString( $this->getCalculatedValue(),
						$this->_parent->getParent()->getCellXfByIndex($this->getXfIndex())->getNumberFormat()->getFormatCode()
			   );
	}
